 Hardware Components:
 
1 Arduino Uno

2 Bluetooth Module HC-05

3 Relay Module

4 16x2 LCD

5 Other Components:
10k Ω Potentiometer x 1
1k Ω Resistor x 1
2.2k Ω Resistor x 1
220 Ω Resistor x 1, Connecting wires

5. Software:
The Arduino IDE is an open-source software, which is used to 
write and upload code to the Arduino boards. The IDE 
application is suitable for different operating systems such 
as Windows, Mac OS X, and Linux. It supports the 
programming languages C and C++. Here, IDE stands 
for Integrated Development Environment.
